Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 2cm slices, then chop into 2cm wide chips (no need to peel). Finely chop the @flat-leaf parsley{1%bunch} (stalks and all). Peel the @garlic clove{1}, pop it into a small piece of #foil with a drizzle of oil and scrunch to enclose it. Remove the @21 day aged British sirloin steaks{2} from your fridge to allow it to come up to room temperature.

Pop the chips onto a large, low-sided, wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the chips nicely spread out.

Pop the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} onto another #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the parcels with the garlic cloves to the tray. Roast on the middle shelf of the oven until the tomatoes soften and the garlic cloves have softened ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once the tomatoes are roasted, pop them into a #bowl, stir in the @French dressing{30%g} and set aside. Once the garlic is softened, pop into a small #bowl along with the @unsalted butter{30%g} and parsley, mash with a #fork until combined.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Season the steaks with @salt{} and @pepper{}. When the oil is hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned, ~{1%minute} on each side. Lower the heat slightly and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want them medium-rare.

> Cook for 1-2 mins more if you like it more cooked.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The steak is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Once cooked, remove the steak to a #plate, top with the herby butter and cover with #foil and allow to rest for a couple of mins. Just before serving, add the @wild rocket{20%g} to the dressing and roasted tomatoes, toss to coat. Share the chips between your plates and serve the steaks and salad alongside. Drizzle any melted buttery juices over the steak. Enjoy!